cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.LG

This paper deals with game theory and computational complexity, which are both central topics in the cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) sub-category. The use of power indices such as the Shapley-Shubik index and the Banzhaf index suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as these indices are often used in multi-agent systems. The discussion of algorithms and computational complexity also points to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental evaluation of the algorithms suggests a connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
